{"title":"Trek’s New Wahoo Path Hybrid Kids Line Helps Create Life-Long Bicycle Riders","link":"https://bikerumor.com/trek-wahoo-path-hybrid-kids-bike/","date":1711557913000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-hero-e1711553439301-800x411.jpeg\" width=\"800\" height=\"411\" alt=\"(Photo's/Trek Bicycles)\" /></p>\n<p>News out of Waterloo, Wisconsin, <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/\" target=\"_blank\">Trek Bicycles</a> has launched a new line of bikes, just for the kids. Trek’s new <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/bikes/kids-bikes/kids-hybrid-bikes/wahoo/c/B428/\" target=\"_blank\">Wahoo</a> Path line of kids’ bikes is packed with lightweight, premium hybrid bikes that ride and feel like adult bikes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new line of bikes sports a light and durable Alpha Aluminum frame, 1×8 drivetrain, adult-style trigger shifters, and confidence-inspiring rim brakes. In addition, the Wahoo Path comes in 20″, 24″, and 26″ wheel sizes, to better accommodate a wider range of kids. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Trek Wahoo Path Highlights</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Alpha-Aluminum.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Alpha-Aluminum-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Wahoo Path Alpha Aluminum\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Alpha-Aluminum-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Alpha-Aluminum-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Alpha-Aluminum-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Alpha-Aluminum-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Alpha-Aluminum.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo’s/Trek Bicycles)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Lightweight, kid-friendly frame</strong><br />The Wahoo Path’s lightweight Alpha Aluminum frame and fork make it easy for the lil’ ones to ride. They’ll have no issues lifting and maneuvering the bike while out exploring their neighborhood on their mini-adventures. Easy maneuverability means keeping things fast and fun. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Excellent Stopping Power</strong><br />Stop on a dime with the familiar, lightweight, and powerful “V” brake, rim brakes. Giving the kiddos a great set of brakes keeps them safe and in control. Resulting in riding with confidence, hopefully creating a lifelong bicycle rider.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-microSHIFT-drivetrain.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-microSHIFT-drivetrain-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Wahoo Path microSHIFT drivetrain\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-microSHIFT-drivetrain-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-microSHIFT-drivetrain-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-microSHIFT-drivetrain-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-microSHIFT-drivetrain-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-microSHIFT-drivetrain.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>A Great Set o’ Gears</strong><br />The <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/microshift-acolyte-1-x-8-speed-group-for-mountain-bikes-brings-riding-back-to-basics/\" target=\"_blank\">microSHIFT Acolyte</a> is a no-joke, kid-specific 1×8 drivetrain with an 11-38t cassette for excellent range. Kid-friendly trigger shifter that’s easy to reach and has a lighter action. Again, setting the lil’ ones up for success, and preparing them for the transition to adult bikes.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Keeping ’em Confident and Comfortable</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The more upright riding position of the Wahoo Path hybrid-style geometry keeps the kids comfortable. The upright riding position allows more control and a better line of sight, for increased confidence. Riding until the street lights come on never looked so good. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Trek Wahoo Path Retail, Sizes and Specs</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-matte-black-e1711553977478.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"428\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-matte-black-e1711553977478-800x428.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Wahoo Path Path 20 blue\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-matte-black-e1711553977478-800x428.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-matte-black-e1711553977478-297x159.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-matte-black-e1711553977478-120x64.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-matte-black-e1711553977478-768x410.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-matte-black-e1711553977478.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-pink-e1711554003170.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"424\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-pink-e1711554003170-800x424.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Wahoo Path Path 20 pink\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-pink-e1711554003170-800x424.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-pink-e1711554003170-297x157.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-pink-e1711554003170-120x64.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-pink-e1711554003170-768x407.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-pink-e1711554003170.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-blue-e1711554019676.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"425\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-blue-e1711554019676-800x425.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Wahoo Path Path 20 blue\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-blue-e1711554019676-800x425.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-blue-e1711554019676-297x158.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-blue-e1711554019676-120x64.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-blue-e1711554019676-768x408.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-20-blue-e1711554019676.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Trek Wahoo 20</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frame:</strong> Alpha Silver Aluminium, 20″</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fork:</strong> Wahoo 20in Alloy, V-brake bosses, ThruSkew 5mm QR</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Shifter:</strong> Microsoft Acolyte SL-M6285, 8-speed</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Rear derailleur:</strong> Microsoft Acolyte M5180S, 34-38t max cog</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Crankset: </strong>Alloy, 28t steel ring with guard, 114mm length</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Cassette:</strong> Microshift Acolyte H083, 11-38, 8-speed</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tires:</strong> Bontrager Connection Comp, wire bead, 30tpi, 20×2.0in</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-viper-red-e1711553905943.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"413\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-viper-red-e1711553905943-800x413.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Wahoo Path Path 24 viper red\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-viper-red-e1711553905943-800x413.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-viper-red-e1711553905943-297x153.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-viper-red-e1711553905943-120x62.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-viper-red-e1711553905943-768x397.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-viper-red-e1711553905943.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-Deep-Dark-Blue-e1711553948998.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"411\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-Deep-Dark-Blue-e1711553948998-800x411.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Wahoo Path Path 24 Deep Dark Blue\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-Deep-Dark-Blue-e1711553948998-800x411.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-Deep-Dark-Blue-e1711553948998-297x152.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-Deep-Dark-Blue-e1711553948998-120x62.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-Deep-Dark-Blue-e1711553948998-768x394.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-Deep-Dark-Blue-e1711553948998.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-blue-sage-e1711553936636.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"413\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-blue-sage-e1711553936636-800x413.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Wahoo Path Path 24 blue sage\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-blue-sage-e1711553936636-800x413.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-blue-sage-e1711553936636-297x153.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-blue-sage-e1711553936636-120x62.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-blue-sage-e1711553936636-768x397.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-24-blue-sage-e1711553936636.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The Trek Wahoo 24</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frame:</strong> Alpha Silver Aluminium, 24″</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fork:</strong> Wahoo 24in Alloy, V-brake bosses, ThruSkew 5mm QR</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Shifter:</strong> Microsoft Acolyte SL-M6285, 8-speed</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Rear derailleur:</strong> Microsoft Acolyte M5180S, 34-38t max cog</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Crankset: </strong>Alloy, 28t steel ring with guard, 127mm length</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Cassette:</strong> Microshift Acolyte H083, 11-38, 8-speed</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tires:</strong> Bontrager Connection Comp, wire bead, 30tpi, 24×2.0in</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Trek-Bicycles-Wahoo-Path-Path-26-White-Prismatic-e1711553820761.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"420\"